Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.53,0:02:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,♪ Aiba Shingun Ka (The Beloved Horse)
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.53,0:01:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,How many months has it been since I left my country? {Kuni o detekara ikutsuki zo}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.14,0:01:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Willing to die with this horse, {Tomo ni shinu ki de kono uma to}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.68,0:01:52.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I have marched through mountains and rivers. {Semete susunda yama ya kawa}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.71,0:01:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Blood flows in reins I took up. {Totta tazuna ni chi ga kayou}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.66,0:02:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,In a pillbox we captured yesterday, {Kino otoshita tochika de}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.12,0:02:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,we are snoring loudly today. {Kyo wa karine no takaibiki}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.58,0:02:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Horse, did you sleep soundly? {Uma yo gussuri nemuretaka}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.97,0:02:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Tomorrow's fight will be tough. {Asu no ikusa wa tegowaizo}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.03,0:02:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,During the war, the creator of this song,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.08,0:02:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,which was widely sung by people who loved its light melody, was Lieutenant General...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.74,0:02:30.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Tadamichi Kuribayashi, the commander of the Japanese army who shook the world during the Battle of Iwo Jima.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.86,0:02:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Only 690 nautical miles from Tokyo, at the southern tip of the Ogasawara Islands.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.63,0:02:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,As the name implies, was used only as a sulfur mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.65,0:02:54.93,Default,,0,0,0,,On June 8th, 1944, General Kuribayashi was appointed as the 109th Corps Commander to protect the island.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.40,0:03:01.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Operation Iwo Jima (Episode 23)
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.70,0:03:12.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for your hard work.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.08,0:03:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.04,0:03:19.48,Default,,0,0,0,,There were no soldiers in Japan yet to shake hands with his subordinates.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.24,0:03:24.47,Default,,0,0,0,,As a military attaché in the United States and Canada,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.47,0:03:31.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Kuribayashi was unique as he was the most familiar with America in the formidable Japanese army.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.94,0:03:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Could I see the island immediately?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.36,0:03:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.36,0:03:50.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The airfield in front of you is the Chidori Airfield. Motoyama Airfield can be seen in the center.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.17,0:03:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,From the west, Mt. Osaka, Mt. Motoyama, and Mt. Tamana. Motoyama is located in the northernmost part.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.46,0:04:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The longest point from the edge of Mt. Motoyama to Mt. Suribachi in the south is 8.3 km.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.36,0:04:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The narrow part of Chidori-gahara is only 800 m.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.47,0:04:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. This is a formidable place.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.65,0:04:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,#MISSING LINE {or he is just sighing here}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.56,0:04:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, the enemy wants it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.44,0:04:17.98,Default,,0,0,0,,This island gives them an aircraft carrier that won't sink.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.98,0:04:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It's also a great place to launch an air raid on Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.27,0:04:22.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Tokyo air raids?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.49,0:04:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,The enemy will start doing it soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.37,0:04:33.78,Default,,0,0,0,,By that time, the US military had crushed the Marshall and Carolyn islands and was now aiming for Saipan.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.20,0:04:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Since the enemy came to Saipan,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.97,0:04:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,General Kuribayashi knew that it was inevitable for the US military to attack the airfield on Iwo Jima,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.38,0:04:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,which is located in the middle of a path to Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.43,0:04:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It was only a matter of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.34,0:04:53.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, could I see the following?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.29,0:04:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.40,0:04:59.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Salute!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.98,0:05:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.29,0:05:16.29,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no river at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.29,0:05:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no water at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.53,0:05:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no water?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.29,0:05:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Only rainwater.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.66,0:05:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,We save it when it squalls to use later.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.82,0:05:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,As a corps commander, Kuribayashi should have been on Chichijima,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.07,0:05:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the most accessible of the Ogasawara archipelago, where his headquarters is located.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.27,0:05:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,However, with the forthcoming American operation to occupy Iwo Jima, he decided to move himself to Iwo Jima.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.74,0:05:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,for the next week, General Kuribayashi toured the entire island.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.52,0:06:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Flat land.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.16,0:06:14.08,Default,,0,0,0,,A cave made of sulfur.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.22,0:06:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And a damp forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.86,0:06:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Meanwhile, American bombers attacking Saipan were raining bombs.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.00,0:07:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The island is almost flat, except for the 169 m Mt. Suribachi.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.89,0:07:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,This makes a good airfield but it will be difficult to protect.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.62,0:07:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,General Kuribayashi used a tactic to destroy the enemy by creating an underground base.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.10,0:07:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The underground base is going to be built 30 m underground.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.79,0:07:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,The large area on the third basement floor here is a hospital.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.94,0:07:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Hospital?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.94,0:07:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And these will be used to communicate between each pillbox.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.42,0:07:52.15,Default,,0,0,0,,The total length is planned to be about 25 km.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.15,0:07:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,The plan is good, but you don't have to make anything 30 m underground.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.20,0:07:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,If it can't withstand a 250 kg bomb, there's no point in making it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.83,0:08:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,However, this island has high geothermal heat and sulfur gas spouts.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.33,0:08:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The other day, when I dug 10 meters to dig a well, it reached 45 degrees Celsius,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.80,0:08:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and the rubber on the shoes of the soldiers melted.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.16,0:08:19.93,Default,,0,0,0,,At that time, we couldn't work for more than five minutes because of how poisonous it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.93,0:08:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. Iwo Jima is probably the most unsuitable place for an underground tunnel to work on the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.08,0:08:33.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But we must do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.24,0:08:39.79,Default,,0,0,0,,If the enemy captures Saipan, they will rush here and then Okinawa with all speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.79,0:08:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Especially because here is right between Saipan and Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.79,0:08:45.54,Default,,0,0,0,,They will definitely plan to launch air raids on the mainland.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.54,0:08:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,To protect the mainland, we have to do whatever it takes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.12,0:08:52.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Please, I want you to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.94,0:08:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The construction had to be done manually.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.39,0:09:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,#MISSING LINES {bunch of background dialog here, not sure if you want to translate it all}
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.08,0:09:22.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, be strong.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.03,0:09:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Next!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.44,0:09:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You could only work for three to five minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.51,0:09:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,A person couldn't continue much beyond that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.46,0:09:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Nevertheless, the construction steadily progressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.82,0:10:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,This exposes the pillbox too much. You had better sprinkle more sand.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.16,0:10:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.67,0:10:09.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy planes aren't just coming to scout, they're taking pictures.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.10,0:10:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,In particular, if there is a pillbox here and there is a moat there, they will mark this as a target in advance.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.02,0:10:18.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, try to disguise yourself as much as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.05,0:10:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.00,0:10:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Air raid! Enemy plane attack! Man your stations!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.14,0:11:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.28,0:11:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Be strong!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.20,0:11:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That night, General Kuribayashi wrote a letter to his wife.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.16,0:11:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,To be brief, I don't think anyone has changed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.60,0:11:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm strong, but I'm living a hellish life.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.98,0:11:54.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Enemy air raids are happening every day.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.82,0:11:57.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They will land on this island soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.68,0:12:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,The soldiers on the island are all prepared.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.40,0:12:08.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course I am, but I am still a weak person.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.06,0:12:14.20,Default,,0,0,0,,When it comes to the game of death, I'm still most concerned about the family.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.82,0:12:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, please take good care of yourself and live as long as possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.55,0:12:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for serving me for a long time.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.19,0:12:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I leave the children to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.56,0:12:39.66,Default,,0,0,0,,He knew it was an imminent situation, but Iwo Jima was too terrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.78,0:12:46.06,Default,,0,0,0,,He has clearly told his family that his bones will be buried on this island.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.18,0:13:01.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The US military had clarified its intention to occupy Saipan, Guam, Tinian, and the Mariana Islands
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.42,0:13:08.85,Default,,0,0,0,,as a foothold for air raids on Japan, in order to use Iwo Jima as its midway station.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.90,0:13:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,In order to strengthen Iwo Jima, the military dispatched a tank corps led by Lieutenant Colonel Seibu,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.77,0:13:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the winner of the Olympic equestrian, along with Major General Rinosuke Ichimaru, a well-known pilot,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.82,0:13:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,to lead the Marine Corps and the engineering corp of the 27th Air Corps.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.76,0:13:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,In this way, 20 square kilometers of Iwo Jima were protected by 15,500 Army personnel
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.39,0:13:48.73,Default,,0,0,0,,and 7,000 Navy personnel, centered on Kuribayashi's 109th unit.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.93,0:13:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,At the end after the reinforcements had been gathered, a supreme operations conference was held.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.32,0:14:05.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Your support is not such a pleasure as a true corps commander.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.17,0:14:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, I would like to obtain the support of various officials in defending to the death this island.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.76,0:14:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,As the officials have already seen, there are no natural fortresses to really protect, just flat lands.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.89,0:14:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So I built an underground fortress, and my goal was to protect it for as long as I can until the last man.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.93,0:14:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I am surprised at the wonderful positions you have constructed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.06,0:14:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what kind of strategy would you employ if the enemy attacked you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.93,0:14:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,According to our Army's standard doctrine, in the case of island defense
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.32,0:14:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,we would have our guns lined up toward the coast and bombard the approaching fleet,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.16,0:14:50.45,Default,,0,0,0,,but I abandoned this idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.45,0:14:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.45,0:15:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,We have 12 320 mm cannons, 22 150 mm cannons, and others less than 15 cms.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.46,0:15:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,These will only damage ships, not sink them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.16,0:15:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, our plan is to let them land, lure them to the center of the island, and destroy them.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.58,0:15:15.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. I agree.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.97,0:15:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.72,0:15:19.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So I have another request.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.43,0:15:21.98,Default,,0,0,0,,No Banzai charges.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.98,0:15:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.65,0:15:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how few soldiers you have, we will not leave our positions and attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.96,0:15:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,We have been taught to do a Banzai charge at the end. But this only hastens defeat.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.06,0:15:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Our mission is to protect the island for as long as we can, be that a day or half a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.70,0:15:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't forget this point.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.72,0:15:52.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I will make the final decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.12,0:15:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Until then, I want you to protect your position and fight with the intention of each soldier killing 10 people.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.72,0:16:00.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's do it according to your words.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.52,0:16:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, instead of defeating the enemy on the beach,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.34,0:16:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,after careful consideration on how to extend the length of defense, it was decided to have a decisive mainland battle.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.08,0:16:19.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Kuribayashi may have wanted to make up his mind and go out with a Banzai charge,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.54,0:16:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,like the analogy of cherry blossoms, {falling cherry blossoms perhaps?}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.58,0:16:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But he made the decision to abandon his innocence.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.32,0:16:33.88,Default,,0,0,0,,On February 19th, 1945, the morning came to Iwo Jima.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.76,0:16:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The sea shining offshore was flooded with 75,144 Marines from the third, fourth, and fifth American Divisions.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.20,0:16:54.45,Default,,0,0,0,,The support fleet consisted of 495 ships with 17 large aircraft carriers
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.45,0:17:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,under the command of Vice Admiral Mitscher, and 111,300 support personnel.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.34,0:17:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Chief of the Navy Forestal was wary of expending too much effort in the bombardment,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.51,0:17:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,especially by the participating ships.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.28,0:17:21.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We fired so much these last three days. I would have expected, the Japanese army to have fled.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.91,0:17:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,No, they have not disappeared. They are lurking in a cave somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.08,0:17:37.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Over the three days leading up to this day, 20 square kilometers of Iwo Jima have already been bombarded.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.75,0:17:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,120 tons of bombs, 2,254 rockets, and 100 napalm strikes from the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.52,0:17:54.92,Default,,0,0,0,,38,550 shots from 16-inch to 35-inch guns were fired from all manner of ships.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.01,0:18:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,With this as a signal, 500 landing craft and 15,000 Marines were sent in with the first wave.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.82,0:18:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Start the attack!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.65,0:19:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Under the command of General Kuribayashi, the operation was successful,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.22,0:19:46.78,Default,,0,0,0,,and the death toll of the US. Army had already
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.78,0:19:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,climbed to include 2,420 casualties, 35 tanks and armored vehicles, and 100 landing craft.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.13,0:19:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition, more than 30,000 US troops had landed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.70,0:20:20.66,Default,,0,0,0,,The US Army advanced to Mt. Suribachi, Chidori Airfield, and Motoyama.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.04,0:20:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Even the U.S. Army couldn't make an advance against the caves of General Kuribayashi.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.63,0:21:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet, on the 23rd, after 20 nights of fierce fighting,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.74,0:21:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Mt. Suribachi, the highest mountain on Iwo Jima, was finally taken.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.45,0:21:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,All the Japanese troops who tried to prevent this had died in Banzai charges.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.91,0:21:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Mt. Suribachi has fallen. The entire island can be occupied with just a few more kilometers.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.86,0:21:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,However, it took 23 days to advance that few kilometers.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:53.80,0:22:02.06,Default,,0,0,0,,{Not sure what song is playing. It does not sound like the one from the start of the episode, but maybe it is?}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.83,0:22:02.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The Japanese army, which had run out of water, food, and ammunition, is finally exhausted.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.49,0:22:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It was around this time that a song of encouragement arrived on the radio from the mainland.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.36,0:22:21.88,Default,,0,0,0,,But how many people were left to respond to this encouragement?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.42,0:22:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Only the northern point remained, and Kuribayashi sent a word of farewell to Tokyo.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.52,0:22:43.32,Default,,0,0,0,,The battle is entering its final chapter.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.88,0:22:47.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We have run out of bullets, water, and food.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.03,0:22:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I would like to say goodbye to those who can still fight now as they are about to make their final move.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.44,0:23:07.80,Default,,0,0,0,,On the night of the 17th, we will make our stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.80,0:23:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Without care for his own personal safety, he issued an attack order that he would spearhead and continued to fight.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.27,0:23:20.58,Default,,0,0,0,,On the morning of the 27th, he killed himself with a pistol
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.58,0:23:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,along with his Chief of Staff Takaishi and Chief of Staff Nakane.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.36,0:23:31.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though he fell, the decision of General Kuribayashi,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.27,0:23:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,who though his command was decreased both physically and mentally,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.42,0:23:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,did not allow the Banzai charge. He took the lead himself, and continued to fight until the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.50,0:23:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The result was more damage to the US military than the Japanese army.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.86,0:23:54.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And his decision and the attitude of his commanders are still highly regarded.
